Cluster Analysis on Pokeman game and television data

Pokeman_trs <- Pokeman_isi %>%
  dplyr::select(HitPoints, Attack, Defense, SpecialAttack,SpecialDefense,Speed)

Pokeman_trs <- na.omit(Pokeman_trs)
# Initialize total within sum of squares error: wss
wss <- 0

# Look over 1 to 15 possible clusters
for (i in 1:15) {
  # Fit the model: km.out
  km.out <- kmeans(Pokeman_trs, centers = i, nstart = 20, iter.max = 50)
  # Save the within cluster sum of squares
  wss[i] <- km.out$tot.withinss
}

# Produce a scree plot
plot(1:15, wss, type = "b", 
     xlab = "Number of Clusters", 
     ylab = "Within groups sum of squares")

# Select number of clusters (2, 3, 4 probably OK)
k <- 3

# Build model with k clusters: km.out
km.out <- kmeans(Pokeman_trs, centers = k, nstart = 20, iter.max = 50)

ggplot(Pokeman_trs,aes(Defense,Speed,col=as.factor(km.out$cluster))) + geom_point() + labs(title="k-means clustering of Pokemon with 3 clusters")
